article.headline: Eastern Illinois 56, Idaho State 53
article.story: RENO, Nev. (AP) -- Cortez Fortes' steal and dunk at the buzzer preserved Eastern Illinois' 56-53 victory over Idaho State in the first round of the Dodge Holiday Classic on Friday night. Bobby Catchings led Eastern Illinois with 11 points while Forte and Josh Gomes each added 10 points for the Panthers (4-3). Slim Millien scored 18 points and had eight rebounds for Idaho State (3-5), whose only lead was 2-0. The Bengals trailed by as many as 11 points in the second half but fought back to make it a one-point game with back-to-back 3-pointers by Jeff Gardner and Arzelle Lewis. Idaho State's chance to win it at the end fizzled when Forte stole the ball from Gardner in the backcourt and raced for the dunk at the horn. Eastern Illinois advanced to the championship game Saturday night against the winner of Friday's nightcap between Nevada and Florida Atlantic.
